         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot. Gard[en] ¶ editorial addition— MS damaged. ¶ 21. Sept. 1857. ¶ Dear Mr Archer ¶  ¶ I am much obliged for your kind attention to Major General M'Arthurs request. If I am not too much int...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">57.09.21</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Henry Archer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">2/137/1, Archer papers, University of Melbourne Archives.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne bot. Gard[en]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>— MS damaged.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">21. Sept. 1857.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Mr Archer</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am much obliged for your kind attention to Major General M'Arthurs request. If I am not too much intruding on you, will you let me have one or two small parcels more of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #000000; ">Zuly</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; color: #000000; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Zulu?<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Archer, in a letter to the editor (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 2 October 1856, p. 6), offered to supply seeds of 'Zulu-Caffre Imphee' obtained 'from a near relative'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>In B72.07.01 and later editions<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M gives the vernacular name 'Caffir corn'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Andropogon saccharatus</seg>;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but see n. 7 below.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #000000; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Imphee</seg>?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I send you 12 packages of Cotton seed, which you probably can distribute without expense to the applicants for the Holcus simultaneously.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[I]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>— MS damaged.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>am sorry, that your name was omitted as a donor to the gardens. You will however observe, that I said, minor gifts had been received from other gentlemen.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B57.09.01.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Previous to my taking the responsibility of administrating this establishment, the books were but laxely kept, and thus I am aware of the incompleteness of the list of Mr Dallachi.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. J. Dallachy.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have however alluded to the Holcus as distributed th[anks] to your<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">assiduity</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in [the] paper on introductions of plants, […]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">illegible<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>— MS damaged.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>at the last meeting of our institute.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The reading of M's paper, B58.05.02, was postponed at the monthly meeting of the Philosophical Institute, 2 September, until 30 September (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Transactions of the Philosophical Institute of Victoria</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">, vol. 2</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(1858),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>pp. xl, xliii). In the paper M remarked: 'Amongst grains I may also briefly allude to the Chinese Sugar-grass (Holcus sacharatus), of which the Caffir variety has been lately distributed throughout the country by Mr. Archer's assiduity, under a desire of adding to the vegetable treasures of the colony' (p. 96).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Is it not possible to get through your friends abroad occasionally a few seeds of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">trees</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>or<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">shrubs</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of rarer kinds, for which we would be able to offer always an good equivalent. We do not care much for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">annual</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>seeds, unless from useful species</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Obediently yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Holcus</p>
         </div>
      </body>
